          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Retail Justice Review Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Justice to study the effectiveness of retail theft rehabilitation programs. A retail theft rehabilitation program is an education program that a retailer offers to a shoplifter instead of reporting a theft to law enforcement. </p> <p>Additionally, the bill states that a retailer may offer a retail theft rehabilitation program in accordance with state, local, and tribal law.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
